    <div class="list-text">
    <a
    class="hed-heading -excerpt"
    href="https://foreignpolicy.com/2018/12/31/the-united-states-cant-rely-on-turkey-to-defeat-isis-kurds-syria-ypg-erdogan/">
    <h3 class="hed">The United States Can’t Rely on Turkey to Defeat ISIS</h3>
</a>
<div class="dek-heading -excerpt">
    <p class="dek">Erdogan wants to confront the Kurds, not the Islamic State. Outsourcing the battle to Ankara will endanger America.</p>
</div>
<div class="meta-data -excerpt">
        <a
        href="https://foreignpolicy.com/category/analysis/argument/"
        class="department-name -excerpt">
        Argument    </a>
        <span class="separator">|</span>
        <address class="author-list -excerpt">
    <a
        href="https://foreignpolicy.com/author/colin-p-clarke/"
        rel="author"
        class="author">
    Colin P. Clarke</a><span class="separator">,</span> <a
        href="https://foreignpolicy.com/author/ahmet-s-yayla/"
        rel="author"
        class="author">
    Ahmet S. Yayla</a></address>

</div>
    </div>
</div>
            </div>
            
                    <div class="blog-list-layout" data-post-id="956060">
                <div class="excerpt-content--list content-block" data-post-id="956060">
    <figure class="figure-image -nocaption">
            <a
            style="padding-bottom:66.666666666667%;
        "
                    href="https://foreignpolicy.com/2018/12/31/amos-oz-israel-ayelet-tsabari/"
                class="image-attachment -ratioscale  horizontal-orientation">
        <img
            data-sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px"
            data-srcset="https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/GettyImages-53473902-1.jpg?quality=90 1500w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/GettyImages-53473902-1.jpg?resize=150,100&amp;quality=90 150w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/GettyImages-53473902-1.jpg?resize=550,367&amp;quality=90 550w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/GettyImages-53473902-1.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=90 768w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/GettyImages-53473902-1.jpg?resize=400,267&amp;quality=90 400w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/GettyImages-53473902-1.jpg?resize=401,267&amp;quality=90 401w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/GettyImages-53473902-1.jpg?resize=800,533&amp;quality=90 800w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/GettyImages-53473902-1.jpg?resize=275,183&amp;quality=90 275w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/GettyImages-53473902-1.jpg?resize=325,217&amp;quality=90 325w, https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/GettyImages-53473902-1.jpg?resize=600,400&amp;quality=90 600w"
            data-src="https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/GettyImages-53473902-1.jpg?w=800&#038;h=533&#038;quality=90"
            sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px"
            src=""
            alt="Israeli writer and peace activist Amos Oz in Frankfurt, Germany, in 2005. (Thomas Lohnes/AFP/Getty Images)"
            style="width:auto;"
            class="image -fit -lazy"
        >
        <noscript>
            <img
                src="https://foreignpolicy.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/GettyImages-53473902-1.jpg?w=800&#038;h=533&#038;quality=90"
                alt="Israeli writer and peace activist Amos Oz in Frankfurt, Germany, in 2005. (Thomas Lohnes/AFP/Getty Images)"
                class="image -fit-3-2">
        </noscript>
        </a>
        </figure>
    <div class="list-text">
    <a
    class="hed-heading -excerpt"
    href="https://foreignpolicy.com/2018/12/31/amos-oz-israel-ayelet-tsabari/">
    <h3 class="hed">How the Mighty Have Fallen</h3>
</a>
<div class="dek-heading -excerpt">
    <p class="dek">Israeli literary icon Amos Oz died on Dec. 28 at age 79. Author Ayelet Tsabari considers his legacy.</p>
</div>
<div class="meta-data -excerpt">
        <a
        href="https://foreignpolicy.com/category/analysis/argument/"
        class="department-name -excerpt">
        Argument    </a>
        <span class="separator">|</span>
        <address class="author-list -excerpt">
    <a
        href="https://foreignpolicy.com/author/ayelet-tsabari/"
        rel="author"
        class="author">
    Ayelet Tsabari</a></address>

</div>
    </div>
</div>
            </div>
            
                    <div class="blog-list-layout" data-post-id="956052">
                <div class="excerpt-content--list content-block" data-post-id="956052">
    <figure class="figure-image -nocaption">
            <a
            style="padding-bottom:66.666666666667%;
